# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Module Map

This profile maps the common code lanes for a React frontend over ERPNext.

## Core Paths

| Path | Responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `{{APP_SHELL_PATH}}` | app shell, initialization, session and global layout |
| `{{API_LAYER_PATH}}` | centralized ERPNext integration layer |
| `{{STATE_LAYER_PATH}}` | global front-end state |
| `src/components/` | reusable components and local interaction logic |
| `src/tabs/` or `src/pages/` | feature-level UI flows |
| `{{STATUS_FILE}}` | current project state |
| `{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}}` | change-record index and rules |

## Modification Rules

- integration changes should land in `{{API_LAYER_PATH}}`
- shell and initialization changes should land in `{{APP_SHELL_PATH}}`
- cross-page state changes should land in `{{STATE_LAYER_PATH}}`
- feature-specific UI should stay in page or component layers

## Coordination Rule

If a request changes both product behavior and project rules, update:

1. code
2. runbooks or architecture docs if the new behavior is durable
3. `{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}}`
4. `{{STATUS_FILE}}`
